metadata.name: Night
metadata.description:
It was a crisp spring evening. The stars glistened in the sky, and the breeze was warm on my skin.

He held me close to him as we walked along the edge of the river. There was just enough light from the moon to see his face as he looked down at me with his deep brown eyes.

He whispered that he didn't want to let me go, and I knew then that I loved him more than anything else in the world.
